      "content": "Modern historians would likely view the UN as a largely ineffective institution when it comes to preventing major conflicts in the 21st century. Despite its noble goals, the UN has been hamstrung by the veto power of its permanent Security Council members, leading to inaction in critical situations. Additionally, the organization has often been criticized for its inability to enforce its resolutions, as seen in conflicts like Syria and Yemen. The UN's bureaucratic inefficiencies and lack of military power further diminish its role as a peacekeeper. Overall, while the UN has had some successes, its track record in preventing major conflicts is far from stellar.",
